## Ali's only action this morning

> The structural defenses from v2 are still intact: `audio-required-gate` filters scenarios/briefs missing audio at both client and server level. So even if turn audio coverage is partial, students will only see fully-audio-ready content.

1. **Open `/admin/retention`** — admin master switch UI on prod.
2. **Toggle Module 4 (Streak) ON for المجموعة 4** — same as v2, lowest blast radius.
3. **Enable streak cron**:
   ```sql
   SELECT cron.alter_job(jobid, active => true)
   FROM cron.job WHERE jobname = 'retention-daily-run';
   ```
4. **Watch 24h**: `system_errors WHERE service='retention_daily_run'` → expect 0.
5. **Add Module 2 (Smart Homework)** for المجموعة 4 next — homework exercise bank is now {{EXERCISES}} strong.
6. **Add Module 5 (Lesson Briefs)** — brief audio coverage is {{BRIEF_AUDIO}}/48. If <48, the audio-required gate hides briefs without audio (they'll come online as audio backfills run).
7. **Add Module 1 (Daily Partner)** — scenarios with full-audio coverage will appear; others hidden until backfill.
8. **Add Module 3 (Weekly Reports)** after any group has 7+ days of activity.

